Run the helper directly from the current project directory:

```powershell
powershell -ExecutionPolicy Bypass -File .\.agents\skills\1c-workflow\scripts\agent-1c.ps1 -Action status
```

On success, return a structured Russian Markdown report with no prose paragraphs. Use the headings `Git`, `Контекст разработки`, `Проверка`, `MCP`, and `Worktree` only when the helper prints matching data, with one `- Подпись: значение` field per line. Translate field labels and structural status words into Russian, but preserve concrete helper values such as paths, branches, client names, MCP identifiers, and result files. Render helper markers as `<нет>`, `<никогда>`, and `<не задано>` instead of `<none>`, `<never>`, and `<not set>`. Include the current Git branch and worktree state; current/main worktree paths, branch type, extension, and infobase; verification freshness and result paths; MCP freshness/status; and every printed active worktree name and path. When the helper prints `Kilo Browser Automation`, copy its Russian state/source line and any following Browser recommendation verbatim under `MCP`; never omit, reword, or move either line. Omit unavailable sections. If the helper fails, report the actual error. Do not switch folders automatically.
